benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion Flows: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04-TC07 cover removal of all and specific tags with various tagDef states and extra parameters.

Error Handling and Validation: TC08 (not found) and TC09 (invalid invoiceItemId format) and TC12 (service unavailable) and TC13 (malformed tagDef) and TC15 (malicious headers) and TC16 (partial tagDef) cover invalid inputs, missing/invalid headers, and edge cases.
Authorization/Headers Handling: TC10 (missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header) and TC11 (invalid/expired authentication token) cover authentication errors.
Edge Cases and Parameter Handling: TC04 (no tags), TC05 (tag IDs not present on the item), TC06 (empty tagDef), TC07 (extra parameters), TC14 (very large tagDef list).
Concurrency/Performance: TC17 high-concurrency test demonstrates performance under load.
Resilience/Integration/Accessibility: TC12, TC18, TC19, TC20 cover service unavailability and accessibility considerations.
gaps: Explicit concurrency edge-cases and race-condition scenarios beyond high-concurrency test.
Soft delete semantics (whether deletions are hard or soft) not tested.
Authorization: lack of 403 Forbidden test for insufficient permissions.
Caching behavior and headers (ETag, Cache-Control) not tested.
Pagination handling not applicable to this endpoint and not tested if dataset grows.
recommendations: Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient permissions.
Add rate-limiting tests (429) and throttling behavior.
Introduce tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and related responses.
Add tests to validate soft-delete semantics if applicable to invoice item tags.
Add explicit race-condition tests for concurrency beyond high-concurrency scenario.
Clarify integration design in TC19: ensure expected status (204 vs 207) aligns with implementation.
